@JacobAndCo. unveils the Godfather II, a $440,000 musical timepiece that brings cinema to the wrist.
Drawing inspiration from one of film’s most iconic sagas, the watch integrates two legendary compositions — The Godfather’s Waltz and The Godfather Love Theme — played through an intricate, built-in music box.
Encased in a sculpted Art Deco-inspired design, the piece combines horological artistry with cinematic storytelling. A flying tourbillon, dual power reserves, and a newly engineered movement elevate both its technical and aesthetic appeal, while the dial features a finely detailed portrait of Don Corleone alongside subtle references to the film’s legacy.
Limited to just 74 pieces, in tribute to the 1974 release of The Godfather Part II, the timepiece stands as a rare collector’s creation, where music, craftsmanship, and heritage converge.
@JacobAndCo #JacobAndCo

Louis Vuitton has unveiled its latest high jewelry collection, Mythica, during a sunset presentation at Kasbah D’If, set against the edge of the Moroccan desert. Conceived as a narrative of personal evolution, the collection is defined by bold geometric forms and an elevated selection of rare gemstones, including natural zircon and fluorescent diamonds.
Central to the collection is the Fortune theme, introduced with House ambassador Ana de Armas. A defining piece, the high-collar necklace, reflects a signature Louis Vuitton High Jewelry silhouette. It is set with more than 4,700 pavé diamonds arranged in a gradient that transitions from vivid orangey yellow to white. Crafted in gold using a snow-setting technique, the necklace is anchored by a 5.12-carat D IF LV Monogram Star-cut diamond, underscoring the House’s emphasis on technical precision and exceptional stones.
